# EvairSIM Flutter App тАФ Project Overview

## Product Scope (CURRENT тАФ April 21 2026, post-pivot-reversal)

> History: An April 19 2026 pivot removed the in-app eSIM marketplace. On
> April 21 2026 Jordan reversed that decision тАФ the Flutter APP is now
> product-parity with the H5 marketplace for eSIM, while keeping the
> physical-SIM activation flow.

The app does TWO things, switched by the SIM Card / eSIM toggle in HomeShell:

### eSIM tab тЖТ marketplace (PRIMARY, H5 parity)
1. Customer browses by country or hot packages on `EsimShopPage`
   (`lib/presentation/pages/shop/esim_shop_page.dart`).
2. Tapping a package тЖТ `/checkout` (existing `CheckoutPage`) тЖТ email
   capture тЖТ payment тЖТ `/order-confirmation`.
3. Backend issues the eSIM, emails the LPA code, and the new SIM appears
   in `My SIMs` (deep link from order confirmation).
4. Customer who already received an eSIM by email uses the small
   "Already got one by email? Connect" link inside the shop, which
   reaches the legacy `/connect-esim` bind page.

### SIM Card tab тЖТ bind / activate physical PCCW SIM (UNCHANGED)
1. Customer buys PCCW physical SIM from Amazon / Temu / Jordan's website
   (NOT in-app тАФ physical-goods checkout still out of scope).
2. 3-step wizard (Scan barcode тЖТ Confirm тЖТ Done) binds the ICCID.
3. Top up using admin-portal-managed recharge packages.

### Still OUT of scope
- тЭМ Physical-SIM in-app purchase / shipping / address forms тАФ Amazon links only.
- тЭМ Mid-pivot "Connect eSIM as the primary CTA" hero тАФ still shipped via
  `BindHeroBlock` for the SIM Card tab's empty state, but eSIM users now
  see the shop instead.

### eSIM 1-Tap Install (added April 21 2026)
The install bottom-sheet (`_InstallSheet` in `my_sims_page.dart`) now shows
a branded "1-Tap Install" CTA on iOS / Android via `EsimInstaller`
(`lib/core/esim/esim_installer.dart`):

- **iOS** тЖТ opens Apple's public Universal Link
  `https://esimsetup.apple.com/esim_qrcode_provisioning?carddata=<LPA>`
  which transfers control to Settings тЖТ Add Cellular Plan with the SM-DP+
  address and matching ID pre-filled. No private entitlement needed.
- **Android** тЖТ tries the lowercase `LPA:` URI scheme; falls back to
  opening the Settings package. A future enhancement can call
  `EuiccManager.downloadSubscription` natively, but that requires the
  app's signing-cert hash to be present in the eUICC's ARA-M file (only
  the SIM CSM can do this at the factory).
- **Web / desktop** тЖТ CTA hidden; QR code shown instead.

The QR code remains as a fallback (button "Show QR code instead", or
auto-shown if the deep-link returns `failed`/`openedSettings`).

### Catalog wiring
- `PackageRepository` + `shop_providers.dart` (already existed but were
  dormant) drive the shop. Endpoints used:
  - `GET /v1/h5/packages/locations` тЖТ countries
  - `GET /v1/h5/packages?location=XX&page=1&per_page=50` тЖТ country plans
  - `GET /v1/h5/packages/hot?limit=12` тЖТ hero grid

### Payment status (open question)
- Web / Android: existing Stripe checkout pipeline works.
- iOS App Store: digital-goods rules require **Apple IAP** for in-app
  purchase. Stripe checkout will be rejected. Replace `CheckoutPage`'s
  payment widget with `in_app_purchase` before App Store submission.
- TestFlight internal builds can keep Stripe for now.

## Tech Stack
- Flutter 3.38 + Dart 3.x, Material 3
- Riverpod 2 (hooks_riverpod) + flutter_hooks (no `setState` for global state)
- GoRouter (StatefulShellRoute for bottom nav)
- Dio + `Either<Failure, T>` (fpdart) for every repository method
- Freezed + json_serializable + build_runner
- Hive + flutter_secure_storage (tokens, locale)
- qr_flutter for QR rendering

## Architecture (Clean)
- `lib/domain/` тАФ entities + repository interfaces (pure Dart)
- `lib/data/` тАФ Dio APIs + repository impls (depends on domain)
- `lib/presentation/` тАФ pages, widgets, Riverpod providers, controllers
- `lib/core/` тАФ theme, i18n, router, network, error, constants

Never import presentation from data/domain. Never import data from domain.

## Backend API base
`https://evair.zhhwxt.cn/api` тАФ the client adds the `/v1/...` prefix per-endpoint.

### Endpoints we consume (customer side)
Auth (`/v1/h5/auth/*`):
- login / register / profile / password

SIMs (`/v1/h5/user/*` + `/v1/h5/esim/*`):
- `GET /v1/h5/user/sims` ┬╖ `POST /v1/h5/user/sims/bind` ┬╖ `POST /v1/h5/user/sims/unbind`
- `GET /v1/h5/esim/{iccid}` ┬╖ `.../usage` ┬╖ `.../enable`

Top-up (admin-managed, preferred): `/v1/app/*` with `auth:app` (our token works on both `auth:app` and `auth:h5`):
- `GET /v1/app/recharge-packages` тАФ packages surfaced by admin portal хЕЕхА╝хеЧщдРчобчРЖ
- `POST /v1/app/recharge` тАФ create recharge order for a SIM
- `POST /v1/app/recharge/{id}/pay` тАФ pay
- `GET /v1/app/recharge-records` ┬╖ `/recharge-records/{id}`

Orders: `/v1/h5/orders/*` (eSIM purchase endpoint exists but we don't use it for new eSIMs anymore)

Notifications (Inbox): `GET /v1/h5/notifications` (public, admin-managed щАЪчЯечобчРЖ)

Live chat (Contact Us): `auth:h5`
- `POST /v1/h5/conversations` ┬╖ `POST /v1/h5/conversations/{id}/messages` ┬╖ `GET /v1/h5/conversations/{id}/messages?since=`

Email: `/v1/h5/email/esim-delivery` etc.

